    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like some people say that focusing on the nonviolence and the moral side kinda downplays how much more radical groups like the black panthers or even malcolm x were actually necessary to force the government's hand. do you think the mainstream narrative just skips over the more militant stuff to make the history feel more comfortable/orderly?",
