      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a very common and valid critique that the mainstream narrative often sanitizes the movement by prioritizing nonviolent leaders. Militant figures and groups like the Black Panthers and Malcolm X provided essential, radical pressure that challenged the complacency of the status quo. Their willingness to advocate for self-defense and systemic upheaval forced a deeper reckoning with racial injustice that pure nonviolence alone might not have achieved.",
